                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="13767355" author="stack" created="Sat, 14 Sep 2013 03:54:31 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Patch?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13819355" author="apurtell" created="Mon, 11 Nov 2013 20:43:29 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Want to remove WALObserver for 0.98?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13819365" author="stack" created="Mon, 11 Nov 2013 20:50:11 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Ugh.  I don&apos;t think we can.  Deprecate in 0.96.  Remove in 0.98?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13819383" author="apurtell" created="Mon, 11 Nov 2013 21:01:18 +0000"  >&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;Deprecate in 0.96. Remove in 0.98?&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;+1&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14001573" author="ndimiduk" created="Mon, 19 May 2014 10:32:23 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Closing this as superseded by the more thorough evaluation happening over on &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-10504&quot; title=&quot;Define Replication Interface&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-10504&quot;&gt;HBASE-10504&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14001944" author="stack" created="Mon, 19 May 2014 16:10:52 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=ndimiduk&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;ndimiduk&quot;&gt;Nick Dimiduk&lt;/a&gt; This is a good idea.  Lets make sure we don&apos;t drop it (it is kinda crazy that per edit we call two different sets of &apos;listeners&apos; &amp;#8211; CPs and WAL.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14002682" author="enis" created="Tue, 20 May 2014 01:25:33 +0000"  >&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;Closing this as superseded by the more thorough evaluation happening over on &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-10504&quot; title=&quot;Define Replication Interface&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-10504&quot;&gt;HBASE-10504&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I think &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-10504&quot; title=&quot;Define Replication Interface&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-10504&quot;&gt;HBASE-10504&lt;/a&gt; defines the replication interface, but async to the write path. On the other hand WALObserver is sync to the write path. So if you want to do phoenix-style secondary indexes, you would need sync-style interfaces, no? &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14003049" author="ndimiduk" created="Tue, 20 May 2014 10:27:04 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;You folks think we should keep this one opened then? Can we not support the two different semantics with the same API, just noting the a/sync registration? The async operation still must be queued and pushing the operation to the queue happens inline.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Perhaps wanting to support the two semantics with the same API is overly optimistic.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14003991" author="enis" created="Tue, 20 May 2014 21:22:57 +0000"  >&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;Perhaps wanting to support the two semantics with the same API is overly optimistic.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Yeah, it looks like an overkill for now. &lt;br/&gt;
Do you know whether anybody wants to plug in to WALActionListener?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14004564" author="ndimiduk" created="Wed, 21 May 2014 10:50:50 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;LogRoller and Replication both implement this interface today. I don&apos;t see it used directly in Phoenix or HBase Indexer.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14330745" author="enis" created="Sat, 21 Feb 2015 23:30:51 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Closing this issue after 0.99.0 release. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
